A bad weather alert in the northern regions of Italy, > especially in the North West, was issued by the Civil Protection. Orange on some areas of Lombardy and yellow for areas of six other regions: the same Lombardy, Liguria, Piedmont, Aosta Valley, Trentino Alto Adige and Veneto. The orange alert for hydrogeological risk concerns Lakes and Prealps Varesine, Lario and Western Prealps and Orobie bergamasche. Already in the night a cloud hit Milanese > with pericolating trees and advertising posters fallen in the capital where the firefighters were forced to intervene in dozens of dangerous situations. There are no injuries or major road accidents. In the Varesotto, between Busto Arsizio, Samarate and Lonate Pozzolo a short air trumpet has broken dozens of trees without luck consequence for people.
According to the forecasts, Easter and Easter days will be characterized by a marked instability> with the first African heat in the South, especially in Sicily and in part also in the Centre, and rains and storms brought from the Atlantic currents to the North where there will be an intensification of precipitation on Easter evening with snowfall at altitudes greater than 1400/1500 meters in the western and central area and beyond 1600 meters in the eastern area. The day of Pasquetta in the morning there are other rounds in the North and Tuscany, in extension to the rest of the Centre between lunch and afternoon. In the South, instead, it will be another almost summer day.&nbsp;

