AGI - Last weekend of March that will coincide with Easter holidays. <a href="https://www.centrometeoitaliano.it/"> Centro Meteo Italiano</a>, "The weather conditions will be uncertain on northern Italy, affected by a southern damp flow within the ascending branch of a vast logging stretched from the North Atlantic to Morocco. The so meridian descent of this sacturation is recalling on the Mediterranean in large quantities of saharian pulviscle (desert dust), going to blur the skies making them of an ocher hue". It will be beautiful and sunny at the Centrosud. "According to the latest model updates, Italy will remain "advertent" from the Saharan pulviscle to the day of Pasquetta. To follow the currents will rotate from Western quadrants, favoring the entrance of oceanic air masses, therefore cleaner. The Saharan pulviscle will then abandon the northern skies at the beginning of the week and by Wednesday also the south".
